sentences.english: The roads and aqueducts of Rome have been the admiration of all after ages.
sentences.chinese: 古罗马的大道和高架渠在其后的年代一直受到羡慕。

sentences.english: Maybe the elevated highway was a bad idea.
sentences.chinese: 可能高架公路是个坏的主意。

sentences.english: The Elevated Pedestians' Walk may guide you to all pavilions.
sentences.chinese: 经过园区的高架平台能够利便地来回于各个展馆。

sentences.english: The viaducts are arteries for urban traffic in Shanghai so they are of fundamental importance.
sentences.chinese: 上海高架道路是城市交通的大动脉，其地位十分重要。

sentences.english: Take Inner Ring Road exit Wuzhong Road.
sentences.chinese: 沿着内环高架路，在吴中路出口下。

sentences.english: The platform of new Tai-An Station.
sentences.chinese: 新泰安站的高架月台和站构。

sentences.english: Heavy Lift Equipment, Hoists, Rail tracks-overhead.
sentences.chinese: 重型提升设备，起重葫芦，高架轨道。

sentences.english: A HUGE cloud of dust rose and an overpass disappeared.
sentences.chinese: 一片巨大的灰尘腾空而起，一座高架桥瞬间消失了。

sentences.english: For bridges, elevated highways, tunnels and subways.
sentences.chinese: 桥，高架公路，隧道和地铁。

sentences.english: After the transforming, the drainage ability of elevated roads of the Inner Ring Line has been raised.
sentences.chinese: 通过改造提高了内环高架路的排水能力。

sentences.english: Pedestrians would meander through underground stores and moving streets between elevated highways.
sentences.chinese: 行人将通过地下商场区及移动步道来往于高架路之间。

sentences.english: A road bridge have to carry a lot of traffic.
sentences.chinese: 高架路得承载很多车辆。

sentences.english: Some people park their cars on highway overpasses to avoid flash flooding.
sentences.chinese: 有些人会将车停在高架陆桥上以躲避突发的洪水。

sentences.english: Data cabling is typically routed through overhead cable trays in modern data centers.
sentences.chinese: 数据电缆通常是经由高架电缆盘在现代数据中心。

sentences.english: To avoid the dangers of people or animals, High-Voltage usually adopts high-line transmission.
sentences.chinese: 为防止人畜触电，高压电一般采用高架线传送。

sentences.english: There was a railroad viaduct in Pilsen that was rumored to be haunted.
sentences.chinese: 皮尔森有一座铁路高架桥，传说常常闹鬼。
